comments: Bridges (BKN) firms up over his left foot and marginal contact occurs as Hunter (ATL) moves into the pick.
Johnson (ATL) legally contests Dinwiddie's (BKN) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Dinwiddie (BKN) rests his hand on Johnson's (ATL) waist and marginal contact occurs as Dinwiddie slides his arm away.
Claxton (BKN) makes contact with the ball and deflects it away from Capela (ATL). The arm contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Bridges (BKN) brings two hands to the ball and his left forearm brushes Murray's (ATL) side. The contact at the end of the drive is marginal.
Murray (ATL) reaches across Bridges' (BKN) front as he is receiving the handoff, affecting his SQBR.
Murray (ATL) legally contests Bridges' (BKN) jump shot, making 'high-five' contact after the ball is released.
As Murray (ATL) is losing control of the ball, Finney-Smith's (BKN) extended right leg causes marginal lower-body contact to occur.
Murray (ATL) goes to the ground in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with Bridges (BKN).
Dinwiddie (BKN) brings his hand forward and marginal brush contact occurs with Young's (ATL) side after the gather into the driving floater attempt.
Capela (ATL) extends his hand toward the ball and marginal arm contact occurs with Claxton (BKN) during the rebounding opportunity.
Claxton (BKN) makes clean contact with the ball and blocks Young's (ATL) layup attempt at the basket.
Claxton (BKN) rests and removes his hand from Young's (ATL) back and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Claxton (BKN) brings his hand to the ball and dislodges it away from Capela (ATL) during the rebounding opportunity.
Walker IV (BKN) firms up in Murray's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs as Murray moves into the pick.
Bey (ATL) establishes a legal defensive position in Bridges' (BKN) path and avoids making illegal contact with Bridges during the driving shot attempt.
Johnson's (BKN) forearm brushes Murray's (ATL) back as he launches into the air to retrieve the loose ball and the contact is marginal.
Finney-Smith (BKN) angles over Okongwu's (ATL) pick and Finney-Smith slides his arm off of the offensive player. The contact during the pick is marginal.
Dinwiddie (BKN) moves laterally into Young's (ATL) path and body contact occurs that affects Young's SQBR. The illegal contact occurs prior to Young's upward shooting motion.
Murray (ATL) rests and removes his hand from Bridges' (BKN) back during the screen and the contact on the play is marginal.
Johnson (BKN) attempts to establish screening position and marginal contact occurs as he comes together with Johnson (ATL).
Murray (ATL) jumps in front of Bridges (BKN) to contest the jump shot attempt, and incidental lower-body contact occurs with Bridges' partially extended right leg after the release.
Bridges' (BKN) right leg extends outwards slightly after the release of the jump shot attempt, and marginal lower-body contact occurs with Murray (ATL) as both players return to the floor.
Murray (ATL) extends his hand toward the ball and contact occurs with Dinwiddie's (BKN) right arm, which alters his driving shot attempt.
Finney-Smith (BKN) extends his hand toward the ball and incidental "high-five" contact occurs after Young's (ATL) release of the driving floater attempt.
Bridges (BKN) rests and promptly removes his hands from Murray's (ATL) back during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Claxton (BKN) brushes Johnson's (ATL) sides as he attempts to establish a legal screening position and the contact with Johnson is marginal.
Johnson (ATL) moves alongside Bridges' (BKN) path and marginal brush contact occurs as Johnson slides his right hand away from Bridges' side.
Capela (ATL) extends his hand toward the loose ball when he makes incidental hand-on-ball contact with Bridges' (BKN) hand to dislodge the rebound.
Bridges (BKN) makes last contact with the ball prior to it falling out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Atlanta.
Murray (ATL) and Dinwiddie (BKN) engage and disengage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.
Bridges (BKN) brings his hand to the ball and deflects it away from Capela (ATL) during the dribble handoff.
Young (ATL) stops and enters his upward shooting motion when Finney-Smith (BKN) continues into Young's space, delivering contact that affects his floater attempt.
O'Neale (BKN) firms up in Hunter's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs as Hunter moves into the pick.
Bridges' (BKN) off-arm comes out slightly and marginal brush contact occurs with Hunter's (ATL) front during the drive into the paint.
Dinwiddie (BKN) momentarily brings his hands to rest on Johnson's (ATL) sides and the contact as Johnson attempts to set the pick is marginal.
Young (ATL) steps toward the middle of the paint as he ends his drive and he extends his right arm into Finney-Smith's (BKN) side, which displaces the defender.
O'Neale (BKN) firms up in Hunter's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs as both players come together during the pick.
Young (ATL) brings his arm toward Bridges' (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Bridges (BKN) avoids stepping out of bounds during his drive along the sideline.
Claxton (BKN) firms up in Young's (ATL) path and does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.
Young's (ATL) momentum brings his off-arm out slightly at the end of his drive and marginal brush contact occurs with Claxton's (BKN) side.
Murray (ATL) rests his right forearm on Bridges' (BKN) side and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Okongwu (ATL) jumps alongside Bridges' (BKN) path and brings his hand to the ball and part of Bridges' hand that is on the ball, legally blocking the driving shot attempt.
Claxton (BKN) commits a take foul on Young (ATL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Bridges (BKN) firms up in Hunter's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the sccreen.
Johnson (ATL) steps into Bridges' (BKN) path and foot-to-foot contact occurs that trips Bridges during his drive.
Claxton (BKN) commits a take foul on Young (ATL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Walker IV (BKN) firms up over his right leg and marginal contact occurs with Murray (ATL) as he defends over the screen.
Walker IV (BKN) does not release the jump shot attempt prior to the expiration of the game clock.
